getCurrentFileRealName() - Static method in class editoractions.EditorActions
Returns the name of the file currently in the editor, for example 'whoami.txt' or 'Hello.java'
getCurrentFileRealPath() - Static method in class editoractions.EditorActions
Returns the absolute location of the file currently in the editor.
getCurrentFileWorkingDirectory() - Static method in class editoractions.EditorActions
Returns the working directory for the file currently in the editor, so if the file path is '/Users/josephreddington/Documents/junit-workspace/testProject/whoami.txt ' then the working directory is '/Users/josephreddington/Documents /junit-workspace/testProject' (no slash)
getCurrentProject() - Static method in class editoractions.EditorActions
 
getCurrentSelection() - Static method in class editoractions.EditorActions
Returns the currently selected text in the currently open editors what happens if there is no text selected.
getcursorLine(TextEditor) - Static method in class editoractions.EditorActions
Returns the cursor location for a given editor, cursor position is an int defined as the number of times you would have to press the up arrow key to get to the start line of the file
getcursorPosition(TextEditor) - Static method in class editoractions.EditorActions
Returns the cursor location for a given editor, cursor position is an int defined as the number of times you would have to press the left arrow key to get to the start of the file
getEditor() - Static method in class editoractions.EditorActions
 
getFile() - Static method in class editoractions.EditorActions
Returns the file current viewed in the editor as an IFile Object so it can be passed to other calls.
getLineNumberForCharNumber(String, int) - Static method in class editoractions.EditorActions
Returns the line number, given a character number.

Returns the line number, given a character number.
